WEBVTT

00:05.790 --> 00:08.157
Did you fix the sink?

00:08.192 --> 00:10.931
I told you I'd get to it.

00:10.965 --> 00:13.310
- Your hair looks nice.
- Thanks.

00:13.378 --> 00:17.530
- You cut it. Hmm?
- Yeah.

00:20.165 --> 00:21.132
I know.

00:21.166 --> 00:25.004
- Know what?
- I had lunch with her.

00:26.303 --> 00:29.704
You know, we had a couple
drinks ... really bonded.

00:31.941 --> 00:34.043
- Hmm.
- What are you gonna do?

00:34.077 --> 00:36.750
What we always said we'd
do if this ever happened.

00:39.820 --> 00:40.904
No! No, no, no! Please!

00:40.905 --> 00:44.093
Please! Please, don't!
Don't!

00:44.127 --> 00:47.063
Okay. Very nice.

00:47.097 --> 00:49.768
Jennifer, play with him first.
Enjoy it.

00:49.802 --> 00:52.105
Ryan, you don't believe
she'd pull that trigger, okay?

00:52.139 --> 00:55.541
Let's try it again.
No prop gun this time.

00:55.608 --> 00:57.175
Ryan, come on, get up.

00:57.209 --> 00:59.210
Okay, you're... great at dying,

00:59.244 --> 01:01.246
but you got to do it...
again.

01:01.780 --> 01:05.150
Ryan?
Ryan, come on.

01:08.523 --> 01:11.091
- What's going on?
- What?

01:14.129 --> 01:16.666
"Cauda equina" means "horse tail."

01:16.700 --> 01:19.836
- Cauda equina syndrome ...
- Gets its name because all this junk

01:19.870 --> 01:21.671
hangs out of your
spine like a horse tail.

01:21.705 --> 01:22.839
Okay, could you stop playing with this?

01:22.873 --> 01:25.975
Okay ...
what the hell are you wearing?

01:26.010 --> 01:30.445
Alfresco lunch-tray pants.
They came today.

01:30.479 --> 01:33.147
"Alfresco" means
"dining in the open air."

01:33.682 --> 01:35.249
Look.

01:36.585 --> 01:37.985
Something's going on.

01:38.020 --> 01:41.523
Uh-huh.
UPS boxes.

01:41.557 --> 01:43.726
There's your tell, Maura.
What happened?

01:43.760 --> 01:46.529
Okay, let's just get back to Casey.

01:48.098 --> 01:50.566
Shrapnel from an I.E.D.
transected his spinal cord

01:50.601 --> 01:52.135
and is still embedded in there.

01:52.169 --> 01:54.204
Only a cowboy surgeon
would attempt to remove it.

01:54.238 --> 01:55.573
It's hope, isn't it?

01:55.607 --> 01:57.074
How did you know?

01:57.108 --> 02:00.310
Yes.
She e-mailed me.

02:00.345 --> 02:02.847
She wants your kidney ...
for Cailin.

02:02.881 --> 02:06.951
- I haven't responded.
- You don't owe her anything, okay?

02:06.986 --> 02:09.988
It is not your fault that
she's your biological mother

02:10.021 --> 02:13.324
just as much as it's not her fault
that you're her biological daughter.

02:14.327 --> 02:16.128
And that didn't sound right.

02:16.162 --> 02:19.532
You should say,
"I like both my kidneys."

02:19.566 --> 02:21.400
And, "have a nice life."

02:21.435 --> 02:22.936
Hey.

02:22.970 --> 02:24.437
What are you doing out in the rain?

02:24.472 --> 02:27.941
Oh, I couldn't get him to
sleep, so I took him for a walk.

02:27.975 --> 02:31.411
- Aww.
- Ew.

02:31.445 --> 02:33.880
- You do that in the kitchen?
- No, of course not.

02:33.914 --> 02:37.216
Yes. She was just about to put
the head in the garbage disposal.

02:37.250 --> 02:40.886
Wait a minute.
You're messing with me, aren't you?

02:40.921 --> 02:43.556
- No.
- Yeah. Your auntie Jane is a kidder.

02:44.859 --> 02:47.460
What are you doing in the
rain with my grandson?!

02:47.495 --> 02:49.530
Babysitting.

02:49.564 --> 02:51.932
I think when you're the father,
they call it "parenting."

02:51.966 --> 02:54.234
He's fine.
He likes the fresh air.

02:54.269 --> 02:57.205
Oh, come here, sweetheart.

02:57.239 --> 03:01.075
Your daddy loved to play out in
the rain when he was a little boy.

03:01.110 --> 03:02.377
Yes.

03:02.411 --> 03:04.813
- How's Lydia?
- She's good.

03:04.847 --> 03:06.715
I think she's gonna get
a promotion at the Penny saver.

03:06.749 --> 03:08.250
Good.

03:08.284 --> 03:11.153
Aw, no!
I wanted to go to bed early.

03:12.255 --> 03:14.190
Was it a murder?

03:14.191 --> 03:15.657
- Rizzoli.
Dr. Isles.

03:15.692 --> 03:19.261
That's so cool.
Man, she's so lucky.

